    "comment_id": "7425240420554551296",
    "text": "This reminds me of the old phrase \"if it's not automated, it's broken\" - which doesn't consider why the process is broken. If it's broken because it's not needed or is producing undesired results, then better to eliminate the process entirely or redesign the process to create the desired results and automate that instead.",
